about: Hello! I'm a software engineer with 10+ years industry experience working across Enterprise Search, Healthcare, and BioTech. I enjoy fast paced projects and I am eager to run into difficult - and weird - problems. I love prototyping new features and technologies, digging into production issues, working on internal tools, and helping new hires. I've worked on small (1-3) to large (15) teams, and I have been recognized with awards for product testing, cross-team collaboration, and hackathon projects. I write backends in Java, Grails/Groovy or Python, create UIs with frameworks like Vue and React, store data with ElasticSearch, SQL, or MongoDB, branch with Git, test with JUnit and Spock, build with NPM, Maven and Gradle, deploy with Docker, Kubernetes, and Hadoop, and monitor with YourKit, Splunk, Prometheus, and Grafana. Indicative examples of my work include: - launching an internal scientific webapp in AWS ECS fed by data pipelines from AWS Lambda - converting ETL pipelines to horizontally scalable microservices - rebuilding a search application with the ElasticSearch - implementing new UIs in Vue or React - building new monitoring tools - analyzing heap dumps to diagnose production issues. Most recently I worked at Glympse Bio, a medical diagnostics company, where I supported the research team with custom applications and ELN/LIMS support. During that time I worked with lab team members to identify problems in their workflow and find solutions that would save them time and improve accuracy. This led to stepping in as the Lead UX Engineer for a new webapp for data entry and analysis which was received with overwhelming support and praise. Before that I worked as a Product Engineer at Genospace, where nurses and doctors used our applications to quickly identify the right cutting edge clinical trials for their patients while scientists took advantage of our population analytics tools to aid their research. I worked across a number of engineering teams, doing day-to-day development and taking the lead on special projects. Previously at Attivio I was a client-facing services engineer tasked with delivering custom solutions with an Enterprise Search Platform. I was exposed to a variety of projects across different customers and industries. My responsibilities included product architecture, client-specific development, and coaching on platform best practices. In my free time I like to climb up rocks, ski down snow, cycle on pavement, and play with cardboard.

about: I graduated from Virginia Tech in 2021 with a degree in Computer Science and Applied Discrete Mathematics, where I learned how to apply mathematical concepts and algorithms to solve complex problems. Hands-on and hands-off technical leadership as needed. - Software: SOA, REST, Python, C / C++, Java, Scala, Spark, ML frameworks (scikit-learn, pandas), AWS, SQL, Perl, TCL, Linux, TDD, SDLC, Docker, Kubernetes - Hardware: RTL design, Verilog, VHDL, SPICE, FPGA CAD, High-speed serial interfaces, processor architecture.

about: I'm a Senior Software Engineer with H1 Carevoyance, a healthcare business intelligence and sales platform. I'm a full-stack Software Engineer with love for data analysis and a passion for machine learning and web3 tech (blockchain and smart contracts, not prospecting). I'm fluent in TypeScript, JavaScript, SQL/PostgreSQL, Svelte, SvelteKit, NodeJS, ElasticSearch, and API integrations. I have hands-on experience with SVG, D3, and many other models, languages, frameworks, and toolkits. I'm a self-motivated team player who can quickly understand and implement new projects. I love science and technology and am continuously learning and exploring personal advancements. I'm studying for my private pilot's license (goal of 2024). I have over 15 years of technical and software engineering experience in the software-as-a-service (SaaS) and digital marketing domains. I own and operate Wandering Leaf Studios, a data analytics and technology consulting agency. I have additional skills in data wrangling, data cleaning, Extract Transform Load (ETL) methodologies, data science method (DSM), exploratory data analysis (EDA), data visualization (Tableau, Matlibplot, Seaborn), and data modeling (supervised learning, unsupervised learning, linear regression, decision trees, logistic regression, clustering, neural networks, deep learning). I also have experience with the cloud computing platforms Amazon Web Services (AWS) and Google Cloud Platform (GCP). Finally, I'm an open-source maintainer (Open Brewery DB), craft beer lover, tea drinker, and a rescue dog owner.

recommendations:
["Myles Younger “I have known Chris for around 10 years now, both as a friend and colleague. We struck a friendship through a mutual friend and shortly thereafter Chris became the technical co-founder of Canned Banners, along with myself and our third founder Jeremy. Chris' approach to Canned Banners (and all projects and roles I have known him to be a part of) was highly methodical. Chris has a strong ability to patiently understand business requirements (as expressed by a non-technical person), ask the right questions, push back in the right areas, and in the end deliver extremely sound, robust code. Canned Banners' initial product was a cloud-based self-serve online ad builder that ran and generated revenue for years with minimal human maintenance and intervention. On a personal level, Chris is just a very nice, well-rounded guy. Very easy to get along with. He claims to be an introvert, but I don't buy it. Chris has always had an impressive array of personal interests and a diverse group of friends. If you're looking at Chris for a potential role or project, feel free to contact me.”"
 "David Lonjon “Chris hired me to support him on one of his client's project. It was evident from the onset that working with him will be a breeze.
